al nodular hyperplasia (FNH) is the second most common benign liver tumour. Key characteristics include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe underlying cause\u003C/strong\u003E remains unclear, though vascular malformation is suspected to play a role\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe condition\u003C/strong\u003E is benign and has no malignant potential\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EWhile \u003Cstrong\u003Emost cases\u003C/strong\u003E can occur in either sex, there is a strong female predominance with a female-to-male ratio of 8:1\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EUnlike hepatic adenomas, \u003Cstrong\u003Ethe lesion\u003C/strong\u003E rarely undergoes complications like necrosis or haemorrhage\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe condition predominantly affects women\u003C/strong\u003E, particularly those of reproductive age, with oral contraceptive use possibly playing a role\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Focal nodular hyperplasia is a benign liver lesion that predominantly affects women of reproductive age","The exact cause of focal nodular hyperplasia remains unclear but may relate to vascular malformation","Focal nodular hyperplasia rarely undergoes complications like necrosis or malignant transformation"],"references":["Alshaikhli A, Al-Hillan A. Liver Cystic Disease. 2023 Apr 24. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 33620816","Torbenson M, Washington K. Pathology of liver disease: advances in the last 50 years. Hum Pathol. 2020 Jan;95:78-98. doi: 10.1016/j.humpath.2019.08.023. Epub 2019 Sep 4. PMID: 31493428","Chan WK, Chuah KH, Rajaram RB, Lim LL, Ratnasingam J, Vethakkan SR. Metabolic Dysfunction-Associated Steatotic Liver Disease (MASLD): A State-of-the-Art Review. J Obes Metab Syndr. 2023 Sep 30;32(3):197-213. doi: 10.7570/jomes23052. Epub 2023 Sep 13. PMID: 37700494; PMCID: PMC10583766","Yamada